The Knights captain has been rewarded for his domestic performances, as well as his performances for the South Africa &#8216;A&#8217; side. JOHANNESBURG - Knights captain Theunis de Bruyn has received his first Test call up to the Proteas squad ahead of the three match series against Sri Lanka, which gets underway on Boxing Day.De Bruyn has been rewarded for his domestic performances, as well as his performances for the South Africa A side.The 24-year-old scored three half centuries and a century in his last five first-class matches for the Knights and will replace Rilee Rossouw, who s been left out of the squad because of injury.AB de Villiers, who stepped down as Test captain on Monday, has also been left out due to his injury, along with Dale Steyn and Morne Morkel.The Boxing Day Test will be Faf du Plessis first as the team s permanent captain.Fast bowler Wayne Parnell has also earned a recall to the team, after missing out on the Australia series last month.The Proteas Test squad to take on Sri Lanka:Faf du Plessis (captain), Kyle Abbott, Hashim Amla, Temba Bavuma, Stephen Cook, Theunis de Bruyn, Quinton de Kock (wk), JP Duminy, Dean Elgar, Keshav Maharaj, Wayne Parnell, Vernon Philander and Kagiso Rabada(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)